      <scopecontent>
         
         
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         
         
         <p>Collection comprises material relating to and examples of Herbert Silvette's writings, which include short stories, novels, and his work on the English translator Philemon Holland (1552-1637). There is also a large body of correspondence from Archibald MacLeish, which Silvette compiled in <title xlink:type="simple" render="doublequote">The Stiletto Letters.</title>
         
         
         </p>
         
         
         <p>Acquired as part of the History of Medicine Collections at Duke University.</p><!-- OPTIONAL: Use Arrangement clip here for Collection Arrangement section -->
      
      
      </scopecontent>
      
      
